			<div id="introduction">
			<h2>Introduction</h2>
			<p>
				The Alabama Incident Management System (AIMS) allows and encourages ongoing, real-time communication between health facilities (Hospitals, Nursing homes, Community Health Centers, Medical Needs Shelters, and EMS providers), and State Emergency Operations Centers (EOCs), tracking staff, facilities, and supplies in times of normalcy and for distribution in times of stress.
			</p>
			<p><img src="http://placehold.it/320x240" class="img-thumbnail"></p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="summary">
			<h2>Summary</h2>
			<p>
				The Liaison Officer Module allows frequent and quick data input of available resources and/or changes in resources during an emergency. The summary section provides a quick overview of the status of the facility. It also provides a way to filter through the information using the drop down lists. The information is provided in two ways, a graph and a more detailed table below it.
			</p>
			<p><img src="http://placehold.it/320x240" class="img-thumbnail"></p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="status">
			<h2>Status</h2>
			<h3>General Status</h3>
			<p> 
				This is the first screen that is displayed when a user logs in. It displays the current state of the facility, i.e., Open/Sheltered in Place/On Diversion /Closed/Evacuation in Process/Evacuation Complete.  To change a status, select the appropriate status, write a comment in the Comment section if needed, and click the Update button.
			</p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="messages">
			<h2>Messages</h2>
			<p>
				This screen allows for communication between a facility and the regional EOC. In this screen, a user can view messages addressed to the facility, create new messages and reply to a message.
			</p>
			<div id="messages-view-messages">
			<h3>To view messages:</h3>
			<p>
				Navigate to this screen by clicking on the Messages link on the menu. If available, a list of messages addressed to the facility will be displayed in a grid. You may choose which messages you would like to see by filtering them in the Filter By section. You may filter by the Read Status (All, Unread, or Read)(1), by the Message Type (All, General, Public Health Message, etc)(2), and by Message Priority (All, Normal, Response Required, Immediate, Urgent, etc)(3).
			</p>
			<p><img src="http://placehold.it/320x240" class="img-thumbnail"></p>
			<p>
				To view the details of the message, click on the View link next to the message (4).
			</p>
			</div>
			<div id="messages-create-message">
			<h3>To create a new message:</h3>
			<p>
				Navigate to this screen by clicking on the Messages link on the menu.
			</p>
			<p>Click on New Message.</p>
			<p>
				The next screen requires you to compose your message. The message destination defaults to the regional EOC. Select the Message Type (1), select a Message Priority (2), write a Subject (3), compose the message in the Body (4), and click the Send button (5) when you are done as shown below.
			</p>
			</div>
			<div id="messages-reply">
			<h3>To reply to a message:</h3>
			<p>
				View the message as described in the view message section described earlier.
			</p>
			<p>You will see the previous message in the correspondence log.</p>
			<p>Click the Reply link.</p>
			<p>
				Type your reply in the Body (1) then click on the Send button (2) to send the message.
			</p>
			<p><img src="http://placehold.it/320x240" class="img-thumbnail"></p>
			</div>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="beds">
			<h2>Beds</h2>
			<p>
				Click on Beds in the menu to navigate to the beds screen. The upper portion is devoted to data entry and the bottom displays a listing of entries you have previously made. Listed in the data entry portion of the screen are Bed Types. This is a list customizable by your facility's AIMS administrator. This is a standard list across the system. When you first open up Beds, the program automatically selects the top category. To enter data, select a Bed Type on the list. Enter the Capacity, Number Utilized and Number Available. Click Save to save. You do not have to fill in information for all the Bed Types in the list. Just select the one(s) you have information on at the moment. Underneath the data entry portion of the screen is a data grid of previously entered figures, complete with a timestamp for each entry. If you wish to change the existing figures, simply select the Bed Type, retype the accurate figures, and click the Save button, overwriting previous figures. Each time an entry is made, the timestamp will change to reflect the last instance in which you saved data to the system. If you wish to delete an entry, you may do so by clicking the Delete link located at the left side of the related record on the data grid.
			</p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="staff">
			<h2>Staff</h2>
			<p>
				Click on Staff in the menu to navigate to the staff screen. The upper portion is devoted to data entry and the bottom displays a listing of entries you have previously made. Listed in the data entry portion of the screen are Staff Types. This is a list customizable by your facility's AIMS administrator. This is a standard list across the system. To enter data, select a Staff Type on the list. Enter the total Scheduled and the Number Reported. Clicking in the Shortfall text box will calculate the number automatically for you. Click the Save button to save your entry. You do not have to fill in information for all the Staff Types in the list. Just select the one(s) you have information on at the moment. Underneath the data entry portion of the screen is a data grid of previously entered figures, complete with a timestamp for each entry. If you wish to change the existing figures, simply select the Staff Type, retype the accurate figures, and click the Save button, overwriting previous figures. Each time an entry is made, the timestamp will change to reflect the last instance in which you saved data to the system. If you wish to delete an entry, you may do so by clicking the Delete link located at the left side of the related record on the data grid.
			</p>
			<p><img src="http://placehold.it/320x240" class="img-thumbnail"></p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="utilities">
			<h2>Utilities</h2>
			<p>
				Click on Utility in the menu to navigate to the Utilities screen. This section lists things such as telephone, power, elevators, generator fuel, etc. The upper portion is devoted to data entry and the bottom displays a listing of entries you have previously made. Listed in the data entry portion of the screen are Utility Types. This is a list customizable by your facility's AIMS administrator. This is a standard list across the system. To enter data, select a Utility Type on the list. Select the Status and write in a Quantity. Then select a Unit, if one exists. Click the Save button to save your entry. You do not have to fill in information for all the Utility Types in the list. Just select the one(s) you have information on at the moment. Underneath the data entry portion of the screen is a data grid of previously entered figures, complete with a timestamp for each entry. If you wish to change the existing figures, simply select the Utility Type, retype the accurate figures, and click the Save button, overwriting previous figures. Each time an entry is made, the timestamp will change to reflect the last instance in which you saved data to the system. If you wish to delete an entry, you may do so by clicking the Delete link located at the left side of the related record on the data grid.
			</p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="form-response">
			<h2>Form Response</h2>
			<p>
				If surveys and other forms are required to be filled out at your facility, you can select the form in the drop down box at the top of the screen, and the form will be displayed. Enter the amounts required and click on the Save button. Your entries will be displayed in the data grid at the bottom of the screen.
			</p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="requests">
			<h2>Requests</h2>
			<h3>Patient Transfer Request</h3>
			<p>
				Click on Patient Transfer in the menu to navigate to the patient transfer screen. This section allows the user to request patient transfers. Click on New Patient Transfer Request to generate a new transfer request. Fill out the required fields and click send. This information will be immediately available to the regional EOC. Once the EOC finds a location for your transfer, you'll get a message in the Messages section of AIMS. The destination of transfer and means of transport will be updated in a response to your transfer request. To view the information, click on the Response button located at the left side of the related record on the data grid. As with other sections, there is a time stamp that records the last data recorded in this section and the bottom portion of the screen is devoted to tracking all occurrences of patient transfer requests.
			</p>
			<hr>
			</div>

			<div id="general-request">
			<h3>General Request</h3>
			<p>
				Click on General Request in the menu to navigate to the general request screen. This section allows the user to request supplies and other general items. The upper portion is devoted to data entry and the bottom displays a listing of entries you have previously made. To generate a new supply request, select a supply type and a supply from the list, then enter the number needed, and click Save to save the request. This information will be immediately available to the regional EOC. Once the EOC finds the items you requested, you'll get a message in the Messages section of AIMS. The details of the supplies request will be updated in the response. To view the information, click on the Edit button located at the left side of the related record on the data grid. As with other sections, there is a time stamp that records the last data recorded in this section and the bottom portion of the screen is devoted to tracking all occurrences of general requests.
			</p>
